{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"635965dc-feb9-470d-9ef3-7fbf7797b889","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr filter by class name directly:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter ClassName=ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The `=` operator requires an exact match on the class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cb54e76e-3b50-488c-b696-d699bc21543c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question I can answer directly.","outputTokens":154,"requestId":"A032:AFC07:19166A2:1C71AC6:69FE8DBB"},"id":"a2e0f029-757e-4d10-88f4-33731d15ec43","timestamp":"2026-05-09T01:28:31.616Z","parentId":"96a50b5d-edd4-46e0-afdd-3016f2190f35"}
